    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is mitigated by tightened acceptance bounds and a sensitivity analysis demonstrating QoI insensitivity to fixture offset variation. All three QoIs pass the E/uval < 1.96 quantitative acceptance criterion. The assessment team accepts the FEA modeling framework as credible for the stated COU. Package submitted under ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and will be appended prior to final regulatory submission.",
